<topic id='attribute_out-patient_attendance_indicator_for_radiotherapy_data_set.description'>
  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>Attribute: OUT-PATIENT ATTENDANCE INDICATOR FOR RADIOTHERAPY DATA SET - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
  <div>
      <p>
An indication of whether the 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_radiotherapy_attendance">Radiotherapy Attendance</xref>
 requires an Out-Patient Attendance record for the purposes of the 
              <xref outputclass="dataSet" keyref="dataset_radiotherapy_data_set">Radiotherapy Data Set</xref>.        </p>
      <ul>
         <li>
            <div>
               <p>
Where the 
                                <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 has been admitted in connection with their 
                                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_radiotherapy">Radiotherapy</xref>
 treatment, an Out-Patient Attendance record 
                                <b>is not</b>
 required, and National Code 
                                <i>'Out-Patient Attendance not recorded'</i>
 applies.                    </p>
            </div>
         </li>
         <li>
            <div>
               <p>
Where the 
                                <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 is either:                    </p>
            </div>
            <ul>
               <li>
                  <div>
                     <p>
Admitted, but not in connection with the 
                                            <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                              keyref="business_definition_radiotherapy_attendance">Radiotherapy Attendance</xref>, or                            </p>
                  </div>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <div>
                     <p>
Not admitted and attends for 
                                            <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                              keyref="business_definition_radiotherapy">Radiotherapy</xref>
 Treatment as an out-patient                            </p>
                  </div>
               </li>
            </ul>
         </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
then an Out-Patient Attendance record 
                  <b>is</b>
 required, and National Code 
                  <i>'Out-Patient Attendance recorded'</i>
 applies.          </p>
  </div>
</body>
